00:00:11,270 --> 00:00:15,000
viewer discretion is advised]

5
00:00:15,750 --> 00:00:16,690
You know?

6
00:00:16,720 --> 00:00:19,200
I've never done anything like this before.

7
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:20,900
I'm struggling,

8
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:22,010
tired,

9
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,580
and so hot.

10
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:25,320
I want to win it all,

11
00:00:26,090 --> 00:00:28,670
so I started making conversations
with the uncles and aunties,

12
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:29,740
and they started

13
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:31,080
to treat me nicely.

14
00:00:32,820 --> 00:00:33,640
Did you hear that?

15
00:00:34,580 --> 00:00:36,040
I finally have friends.

16
00:00:37,160 --> 00:00:38,560
Such a crybaby, huh?

17
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,160
Jeez, you scared me there.

18
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:11,210
Sila,

19
00:01:11,630 --> 00:01:12,580
what are you doing?

20
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:17,280
Getting back at the little guy
who ditched me.

21
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,440
"Ah,

22
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:29,360
ah!"

23
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:30,880
Like this!

24
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:32,000
Is that true, Pawn?

25
00:01:32,070 --> 00:01:34,310
I heard that Boss likes him.

26
00:01:34,340 --> 00:01:35,960
Boss likes them young.

27
00:01:36,890 --> 00:01:38,880
There's no doubt.

28
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,440
I knew it, that soft-looking newcomer

29
00:01:41,490 --> 00:01:42,789
was living in separate housing,

30
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:44,690
unlike us.

31
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:46,700
That's right.

32
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:50,350
Perhaps he wanted to be
the new Boss Babe.

33
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:52,090
What kind of Boss Babe is that young?

34
00:01:52,130 --> 00:01:53,009
- Oh,
- Whoa!

35
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:54,400
you!

36
00:01:54,430 --> 00:01:55,960
It's true, though.

37
00:01:55,990 --> 00:01:57,620
Quit spreading false rumors already!

38
00:01:57,720 --> 00:01:59,210
I was around there last night, too.

39
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:00,280
What? Where?

40
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:02,320
I was the only person there.

41
00:02:02,550 --> 00:02:04,600
And you guys, don't listen to her too much.

42
00:02:05,530 --> 00:02:07,300
In fact, what really happened...

43
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:34,150
♫But no one sees what's behind my smiles♫

44
00:02:34,570 --> 00:02:38,210
♫It's the loneliness I try to hide♫

45
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:43,600
♫Will there be someone my heart's seeking?♫

46
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:47,470
♫Then today, I got you near♫

47
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:52,250
♫You made my heart drift away♫

48
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:54,230
♫Lost in your gaze♫

49
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:57,710
♫Like a stream washing over me♫

50
00:02:57,740 --> 00:03:03,190
♫Wanna give this a try,
like it's more than one night?♫

51
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:06,800
♫Let's change one night into♫

52
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:08,620
♫Something more, alright♫

53
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:11,770
♫Let's follow our hearts once♫

54
00:03:11,830 --> 00:03:17,660
♫Wanna give this a try, just let me get inside?♫

55
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:23,880
♫Deep inside, I'll make you feel whole♫

56
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:28,460
♫May I ask you to be my last?♫

57
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:43,920
Are you rushing to go
back to your boyfriend, Saitharn?

58
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:50,860
I have to go now.

59
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:51,960
I want to sleep early.

60
00:03:53,140 --> 00:03:54,079
See you tomorrow.

61
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,160
Saitharn.

62
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,880
Saitharn!

63
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:01,600
Did I say something wrong?

64
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:05,630
Did I say anything offensive?

65
00:04:08,150 --> 00:04:08,990
Right?

66
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:12,400
Saitharn seemed fine earlier.

67
00:04:12,510 --> 00:04:13,230
But...

68
00:04:13,890 --> 00:04:16,180
suddenly, he was like, angry.

69
00:04:18,220 --> 00:04:19,220
Did he...

70
00:04:20,149 --> 00:04:21,399
break up with his boyfriend?

71
00:04:25,090 --> 00:04:26,090
Sh*t...

72
00:04:26,970 --> 00:04:28,510
Should we go after him?

73
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,520
I'm a bit worried.

74
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:32,890
Yeah, let's go.

75
00:04:35,090 --> 00:04:35,710
Come on.

76
00:04:46,300 --> 00:04:47,500
What are you...

77
00:04:50,950 --> 00:04:52,000
Let's hide right here.

78
00:04:53,110 --> 00:04:53,880
Why?

79
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,360
We're not thieves.

80
00:04:56,490 --> 00:04:57,080
Look.

81
00:04:57,710 --> 00:05:00,040
Boss is talking to Saitharn over there.

82
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:01,720
So? There's nothing wrong with that.

83
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:03,790
Boss normally comes to
talk to us as well.

84
00:05:04,910 --> 00:05:06,160
At this hour?

85
00:05:06,190 --> 00:05:07,040
Yeah.

86
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:08,530
You're overthinking it.

87
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:09,700
I think...

88
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:11,970
What?

89
00:05:12,670 --> 00:05:13,630
Where is the noise coming from?

90
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,300
Found it.

91
00:05:28,010 --> 00:05:28,680
Ah!

92
00:05:37,909 --> 00:05:38,880
It's gone.

93
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:42,680
That was close.

94
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:44,560
Oh,

95
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,960
so it's you guys

96
00:05:45,990 --> 00:05:47,970
who threw a stick at my face!

97
00:05:48,380 --> 00:05:51,240
How can a gecko be this pretty?

98
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,320
Stop laughing, you two.

99
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,480
Without me,

100
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:57,920
will you get to hear juicy stories like this?

101
00:05:58,070 --> 00:05:59,320
That's nonsense!

102
00:05:59,350 --> 00:06:00,760
They didn't do anything last night.

103
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:02,920
How would you know if they
did or did not do it?

104
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,320
They were alone together;
how could they not do it?

105
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:06,980
They just sat and talked.

106
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:08,570
Even if they did really do it,

107
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:10,480
it's not your business anyway.

108
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,020
Oh?

109
00:06:11,820 --> 00:06:14,000
Are you being this defensive

110
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,610
because

111
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:18,440
you want to be our Boss Babe too?

112
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:22,520
Don't you have anything better to do?

113
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,720
If you have that much time to waste,

114
00:06:23,780 --> 00:06:25,840
then go do your job.

115
00:06:25,940 --> 00:06:27,390
You've been here for ten years now,

116
00:06:27,430 --> 00:06:28,860
aren't you even a little bit ashamed?!

117
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,360
Hey! Don't you dare shout at me.

118
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:31,110
What?

119
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,700
If you won't let me
gossip about our boss...

120
00:06:33,740 --> 00:06:34,720
then I won't.

121
00:06:35,230 --> 00:06:36,060
How about this?

122
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:39,070
I'll gossip about you and Saeng-La instead.

123
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:42,390
If it's you guys,
I don't even have to make up stories.

124
00:06:42,409 --> 00:06:44,390
Because it's already that obvious!

125
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:47,280
Saeng-La!

126
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,440
Saeng-La!

127
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,400
These two...

128
00:06:52,430 --> 00:06:53,720
as if they can lecture me.

129
00:06:54,980 --> 00:06:55,930
I don't care.

130
00:06:56,740 --> 00:06:58,520
Hey, but I really did see it.

131
00:06:58,560 --> 00:06:59,890
It was like, ooh,

132
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:00,480
it's...

133
00:07:01,580 --> 00:07:02,260
Ahh!

134
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:03,990
What the hell do you
think you're doing?

135
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:04,630
I'm going to...

136
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,280
You goddamn...

137
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:08,790
These kids...

138
00:07:08,890 --> 00:07:09,790
Brats!

139
00:07:13,540 --> 00:07:14,840
Am I still pretty?

140
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:18,720
I'm just speaking the truth.

141
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,600
Just forget those brats already.

142
00:07:22,670 --> 00:07:25,120
Help me get rid of the leaves.
Do I look good now?

143
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:28,450
Do you think Boss likes beautiful women?

144
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,670
Will beautiful women like me stand a chance?

145
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:32,000
What?

146
00:07:32,130 --> 00:07:33,320
What are you planning?

147
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:36,860
Well, I might actually stand a chance.

148
00:07:36,890 --> 00:07:38,080
Hmm.

149
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,000
Thinking ahead, huh?

150
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:42,260
I also want to try.

151
00:07:43,690 --> 00:07:45,920
Do I have a chance?

152
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:52,750
Saeng-La.

153
00:07:53,610 --> 00:07:54,300
Saeng-La.

154
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:56,760
Stop walking already.

155
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:58,400
Calm down.

156
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:00,310
Calm down?

157
00:08:00,550 --> 00:08:01,720
She said that to us,

158
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,120
how can I still stay calm?

159
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,400
But what we did

160
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:06,980
is normal, isn't it?

161
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:09,720
Why are you so upset?

162
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:11,640
If what she said is wrong,

163
00:08:12,220 --> 00:08:13,460
then just correct her.

164
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:16,190
Or is it that...

165
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:19,410
you know there's something.

166
00:08:21,630 --> 00:08:22,520
There's what?

167
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,520
There's nothing!

168
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:27,800
Don't just believe whatever she says.

169
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:30,000
She's just spewing bullsh*t.

170
00:08:31,650 --> 00:08:32,600
So you do know

171
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,600
that she's just speaking nonsense.

172
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,220
Then why do you have to get so worked up?

173
00:08:39,179 --> 00:08:40,280
Just let her be.

174
00:08:45,950 --> 00:08:47,080
Can you tell me

175
00:08:48,790 --> 00:08:49,580
what exactly

176
00:08:50,090 --> 00:08:51,310
you are feeling right now?

177
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:01,400
I don't know.

178
00:09:02,420 --> 00:09:04,640
I just don't like how she talks about us.

179
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,480
Or is it that you don't like
what we are right now?

180
00:09:08,090 --> 00:09:08,960
No.

181
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:11,140
When Pawn brought it up

182
00:09:11,430 --> 00:09:12,430
I just...

183
00:09:18,710 --> 00:09:19,710
How about this then?

184
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:21,640
From now on,

185
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:24,760
I'll let Wan and Koen

186
00:09:25,070 --> 00:09:26,160
work with you instead,

187
00:09:26,330 --> 00:09:27,200
if you want.

188
00:09:27,260 --> 00:09:28,440
Are you insulting me?

189
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:30,760
I'm not.

190
00:09:31,730 --> 00:09:33,820
I just want you to feel better.

191
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:37,910
You can tell me

192
00:09:38,030 --> 00:09:38,960
anything,

193
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,810
alright?

194
00:09:41,460 --> 00:09:42,460
I'm always ready to...

195
00:09:42,490 --> 00:09:43,820
You don't have to do anything.

196
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:46,040
It's my feelings.

197
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:49,680
I can take care of it.

198
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:52,480
You don't have to help me.

199
00:10:00,500 --> 00:10:01,120
Saeng-La!

200
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:07,160
[Phusangdao Group]

201
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,920
I can't take this anymore, Sila!

202
00:10:09,140 --> 00:10:11,720
Don't you dare come to my housing again.

203
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:14,560
And I will pack all my things by today.

204
00:10:15,210 --> 00:10:15,920
Why?

205
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:17,520
What happened?

206
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,940
Did someone do something to you?

207
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:23,390
It's you!

208
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:25,120
Why do you have to
come visit me at night?

209
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,530
Do you have any idea

210
00:10:26,550 --> 00:10:28,200
how the others speak of me?

211
00:10:28,710 --> 00:10:29,760
You can visit during the day,

212
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:30,880
so why do you only come at night?

213
00:10:31,450 --> 00:10:32,770
Oh, actually,

214
00:10:32,890 --> 00:10:34,810
you don't even have to come visit me.

215
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:36,200
Let's just say...

216
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,440
from now on,

217
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:39,390
you'll not see me there anymore!

218
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,150
Because I'll move to be with
Mok and Saeng-La.

219
00:10:41,380 --> 00:10:43,910
And I'll finish moving everything by today.

220
00:10:46,530 --> 00:10:48,710
Please calm down, Saitharn.

221
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:51,960
You're too tense.

222
00:10:52,950 --> 00:10:55,620
I don't think anyone here
thinks badly of you.

223
00:10:56,730 --> 00:10:59,900
If you don't believe me,
then ask them about this in a few days.

224
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:01,900
They would've already forgotten.

225
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:05,490
They are simply tattling.

226
00:11:05,610 --> 00:11:06,500
That's all.

227
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:09,010
Tattling?

228
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,600
What does that mean?

229
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:19,490
You don't have to care
what the others think.

230
00:11:20,190 --> 00:11:22,270
I want to hear more from you.

231
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:26,480
What did you do today?

232
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:27,840
Hm?

233
00:11:28,210 --> 00:11:29,800
Working to pay off my debt.

234
00:11:35,210 --> 00:11:38,520
And do you want to pay off
your debt faster?

235
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,890
I have a way,

236
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,460
but it depends...

237
00:11:52,110 --> 00:11:54,090
if you'll be brave enough to do it?

238
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:00,920
Hm?

239
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,160
Whoa!

240
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:21,200
This place is as gorgeous
as it was in the film.

241
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,790
Whoa.

242
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,640
Oh, wow.

243
00:12:45,690 --> 00:12:46,980
I never knew...

244
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:51,300
this farm had such a scenic spot.

245
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,600
It's like we're in a set piece.

246
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:55,400
Of course, it does.

247
00:12:56,180 --> 00:12:57,770
But only a few come here.

248
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:00,860
It'd usually be my dad and no one else.

249
00:13:01,620 --> 00:13:04,280
He always brought me here
when I was little.

250
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:08,240
This spot had always been his favorite.

251
00:13:09,780 --> 00:13:12,440
He'd take me here to
get away from the crowd.

252
00:13:13,770 --> 00:13:16,940
Sometimes, we'd simply
sit here quietly for hours.

253
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:21,090
You seem to be very close
to your father, no?

254
00:13:24,490 --> 00:13:26,200
More than one might expect.

255
00:13:27,870 --> 00:13:30,960
Even though I might not be
a man of many talents,

256
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:35,200
I'm sure that I've always
been his trusted son.

257
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,560
And...

258
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:43,240
How did you end up taking on
the role of the boss here?

259
00:13:46,190 --> 00:13:49,490
I inherited the business
from my father after he passed.

260
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:52,620
That's why I've been managing
Phusangdao Farm full-time.

261
00:13:54,090 --> 00:13:56,280
I remember it well.
I had just graduated from school

262
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:59,080
and had no work experience.

263
00:13:59,420 --> 00:14:01,520
I knew virtually nothing about the farm.

264
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,240
I also had no clue

265
00:14:06,330 --> 00:14:08,120
whether or not I could manage it,

266
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:10,560
but the circumstances forced me

267
00:14:11,930 --> 00:14:13,790
to pull through.

268
00:14:20,290 --> 00:14:22,200
And... how long has it been?

269
00:14:24,370 --> 00:14:25,300
Oh.

270
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:28,240
It's already been 12 years.

271
00:14:28,470 --> 00:14:29,520
Whoa.

272
00:14:30,820 --> 00:14:33,040
That's literally half of my life.

273
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:34,280
I mean...

274
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:37,310
It's more than obvious that you're an unc.

275
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:40,160
But I didn't expect you to be this old.

276
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:42,110
Hey.

277
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:44,440
Who says I'm an unc?

278
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:45,720
This year,

279
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:47,560
I'll merely be turning 35, alright?

280
00:14:48,420 --> 00:14:49,600
Well, that's an unc in my book.

281
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:51,410
You're about a decade older than me.

282
00:14:53,770 --> 00:14:54,800
A decade older?

283
00:14:56,210 --> 00:14:56,720
By the way,

284
00:14:57,690 --> 00:14:58,690
how old are you?

285
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:02,000
I'll be turning 23 this year.

286
00:15:03,150 --> 00:15:04,980
Oh.

287
00:15:06,020 --> 00:15:07,400
Yet, you're acting like an old man

288
00:15:08,430 --> 00:15:10,730
who already knows his place, kiddo.

289
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:12,480
Kiddo, you say?

290
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:16,850
Do you think I'm still wet
behind the ears or something?

291
00:15:17,190 --> 00:15:18,900
Let me tell you something.

292
00:15:19,260 --> 00:15:20,180
Despite how I look,

293
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,240
I'm a heavy-hitter, alright?

294
00:15:23,850 --> 00:15:25,200
No need to tell me that.

295
00:15:25,370 --> 00:15:26,380
I can tell that you're

296
00:15:26,950 --> 00:15:27,950
a heavy-hitter.

297
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,300
Everyone thinks

298
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:38,170
I'm mean

299
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:39,640
and harsh,

300
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,160
throwing tantrums whenever I get upset

301
00:15:44,230 --> 00:15:45,230
and caring about no one.

302
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,080
But no one knows

303
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,380
what's on my mind,

304
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:52,250
what I'm feeling,

305
00:15:52,810 --> 00:15:55,300
or what I've gone through.

306
00:15:58,930 --> 00:16:00,100
Honestly,

307
00:16:00,570 --> 00:16:01,700
even my mom

308
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:05,120
knows almost nothing about me.

309
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:11,220
But you're here now

310
00:16:11,260 --> 00:16:12,560
at Phusangdao Farm.

311
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,600
I'm sure no one here
sees you in that light.

312
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:19,680
Rest assured.

313
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:23,000
Take this as a vacation,

314
00:16:23,370 --> 00:16:25,220
changing up the pace.

315
00:16:26,210 --> 00:16:27,500
And...

316
00:16:33,590 --> 00:16:34,790
You get to stay with me here.

317
00:16:35,210 --> 00:16:36,210
Hold it right there.

318
00:16:37,190 --> 00:16:38,500
When did I say that I'd stay with you?

319
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:43,200
Well, you did during that night

320
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,710
when we...

321
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,280
- We...
- Stop!

322
00:16:49,340 --> 00:16:51,220
Stop it, old man.

323
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:52,320
So is this

324
00:16:52,930 --> 00:16:54,320
how you'll help me

325
00:16:54,350 --> 00:16:55,390
pay off my debt quicker?

326
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:57,390
No, I'm just teasing you.

327
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,200
But...

328
00:17:04,530 --> 00:17:05,359
Tonight,

329
00:17:05,390 --> 00:17:06,599
can I visit

330
00:17:07,690 --> 00:17:08,810
your place again?

331
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,319
Stop it.

332
00:17:15,130 --> 00:17:17,609
The others will...

333
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,000
tattle about me again.

334
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,490
How about this?

335
00:17:24,630 --> 00:17:26,460
Come see me at the main quarter.

336
00:17:28,319 --> 00:17:31,330
This way, no one will dare do such a thing.

337
00:17:34,330 --> 00:17:35,150
Interested?

338
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:35,980
Hey.

339
00:17:38,040 --> 00:17:38,860
Please.

340
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,200
No.

341
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:41,360
Oh!

342
00:17:44,090 --> 00:17:44,900
Ow!

343
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:47,070
Scoot over already.

344
00:17:47,510 --> 00:17:48,320
It's so cramped!

345
00:18:12,310 --> 00:18:14,500
You call this progress?

346
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:20,410
I still don't see how this is
any different from the original plan.

347
00:18:21,390 --> 00:18:23,290
We still haven't heard
anything from K Group.

348
00:18:24,620 --> 00:18:27,420
Are you really just going to let
the other farm close the deal this easily?

349
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:30,780
If they secure this deal,

350
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:32,890
it's over.

351
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,580
Or do you people just not understand

352
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:37,160
how critical the upcoming summit
in a few days is?

353
00:18:39,610 --> 00:18:40,710
Enough, Muang.

354
00:18:43,140 --> 00:18:44,100
Everyone, leave.

355
00:19:02,710 --> 00:19:04,080
Here's a question.

356
00:19:07,190 --> 00:19:08,880
If we cannot put an end to their deal,

357
00:19:09,120 --> 00:19:10,180
what will you do?

358
00:19:11,310 --> 00:19:12,630
I'll take care of it myself, Dad.

359
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:15,440
Sila isn't that tough to crack.

360
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:16,500
Is that so?

361
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:21,280
How are you going to stop him, then?

362
00:19:23,820 --> 00:19:24,920
I have a way.

363
00:19:25,510 --> 00:19:26,720
I know his weaknesses.

364
00:19:29,390 --> 00:19:31,240
Listen up, Muang.

365
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:34,010
What you have right now

366
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,400
is a lot of emotions.

367
00:19:38,390 --> 00:19:39,880
But what I currently have in my hands

368
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:41,520
is a plan.

369
00:19:41,960 --> 00:19:42,840
But Dad...

370
00:19:45,490 --> 00:19:46,120
Well...

371
00:19:47,090 --> 00:19:48,800
If Sila manages to close the deal,

372
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:53,280
his farm will become the main powerhouse
in this region, with no competition.

373
00:19:56,350 --> 00:19:57,440
There you go.

374
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,560
And we must prevent it from happening.

375
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:03,520
Yes.

376
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,020
Listen to me well.

377
00:20:12,450 --> 00:20:14,180
Go and meet Sila

378
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,240
with another deal.

379
00:20:20,910 --> 00:20:22,520
Tell him

380
00:20:24,930 --> 00:20:26,390
we're running a whole new game now,

381
00:20:27,190 --> 00:20:28,960
one that dwarfs what we had with Korea.

382
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,320
If anyone dares to

383
00:20:33,060 --> 00:20:35,240
make Sila hesitate...

384
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,100
Dad.

385
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:39,070
You're telling me

386
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,910
we'll be partnering with him?

387
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,440
Not partnering.

388
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:45,990
We're binding him to us.

389
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,210
Should Sila fail to
find a way out of our game,

390
00:20:50,310 --> 00:20:52,000
he won't be able to leave.

391
00:20:53,390 --> 00:20:54,990
What if he doesn't bite?

392
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:58,990
You are my son.

393
00:21:01,140 --> 00:21:03,240
Everyone has weaknesses.

394
00:21:04,330 --> 00:21:05,560
You said you know his, didn't you?

395
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:11,960
Lure him into our trap,

396
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,960
and he'll fall into it on his own.

397
00:21:20,020 --> 00:21:21,130
Remember this:

398
00:21:23,040 --> 00:21:25,120
never think of yourself as a player.

399
00:21:26,340 --> 00:21:27,580
Sometimes,

400
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:30,310
a pawn is just a pawn,

401
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,060
but the one who wins

402
00:21:36,590 --> 00:21:38,400
is the one who establishes the board.

403
00:21:54,620 --> 00:21:56,160
I'm still full.

404
00:21:56,190 --> 00:21:57,010
Look, Phae.

405
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,370
- That's lovely.
- Oh, it is,

406
00:21:58,410 --> 00:21:59,410
that pink one.

407
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,390
Let's check out the fabrics here.

408
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:03,140
Yeah, I went to look for
some yesterday, but...

409
00:22:03,180 --> 00:22:04,120
Hello.

410
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:06,320
I didn't see one that caught my eye.

411
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:06,990
Oh?

412
00:22:10,010 --> 00:22:11,160
These colors are lovely.

413
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:12,390
Mm.

414
00:22:12,930 --> 00:22:14,190
These colors suit you, Phae.

415
00:22:14,410 --> 00:22:15,320
They look...

416
00:22:15,910 --> 00:22:17,700
- lovely.
- Mm.

417
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:20,210
And...

418
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:21,760
do you like it?

419
00:22:23,370 --> 00:22:24,670
I'm talking about the fabric,

420
00:22:24,820 --> 00:22:25,820
not me.

421
00:22:31,190 --> 00:22:32,940
I love ones with plain and light colors.

422
00:22:34,430 --> 00:22:36,800
But if there are ones
with patterns or bright colors,

423
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:38,590
that would be pretty interesting.

424
00:22:39,130 --> 00:22:39,880
Um...

425
00:22:40,510 --> 00:22:42,010
Hey, Gale!

426
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:44,080
- Hey!
- Jessica?!

427
00:22:44,110 --> 00:22:45,510
Long time no see!

428
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:46,720
Oh...

429
00:22:47,020 --> 00:22:48,940
You're... Mueanphae, right?

430
00:22:49,830 --> 00:22:52,500
- She's the girl who you...
- Oh! This is Jessica,

431
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,410
a friend of mine from Paris.

432
00:22:55,930 --> 00:22:56,880
Oh.

433
00:22:57,210 --> 00:22:58,650
Hey, there.

434
00:22:58,680 --> 00:22:59,960
I'm Jessica.

435
00:22:59,980 --> 00:23:01,440
You can also call me Jess.

436
00:23:01,460 --> 00:23:03,180
- Hello.
- It's nice to meet you.

437
00:23:03,210 --> 00:23:04,320
She sure is lovely.

438
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,850
No wonder

439
00:23:06,000 --> 00:23:07,410
you want to work...

440
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:09,210
What are you doing here
in Chiang Rai again?

441
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:10,760
I'm working on a project.

442
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:12,900
The one I told you about.

443
00:23:13,170 --> 00:23:13,920
Remember?

444
00:23:17,630 --> 00:23:18,690
That project?

445
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,490
Oh... That one.

446
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:23,840
What a lovely project it is.

447
00:23:23,870 --> 00:23:25,840
We have to continue
browsing for fabrics now.

448
00:23:25,970 --> 00:23:26,970
I'll talk to you later.

449
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,050
- Are you leaving already?
- Yeah.

450
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:28,620
Come, Phae.

451
00:23:28,650 --> 00:23:30,260
I haven't told you
how lovely your project is!

452
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:30,780
Yeah, yeah.

453
00:23:30,820 --> 00:23:32,390
- This project is going to be
- See you.

454
00:23:32,420 --> 00:23:34,520
How lovely the support you have there.

455
00:23:34,780 --> 00:23:35,780
Woo!

456
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:37,120
Gale.

457
00:23:37,860 --> 00:23:40,000
Hold on tight,
or you might lose your project.

458
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,400
Mueanphae, bye-bye.

459
00:23:53,190 --> 00:23:55,760
Your friend seemed a bit surprised, Gale.

460
00:23:56,190 --> 00:23:58,210
It was like she knew me or something.

461
00:23:58,900 --> 00:23:59,670
Oh.

462
00:24:00,340 --> 00:24:00,990
Well...

463
00:24:01,820 --> 00:24:03,090
Jess is always too quick to speak.

464
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:04,440
Hm? Why?

465
00:24:04,990 --> 00:24:07,300
You told her about me?

466
00:24:08,030 --> 00:24:10,370
Mm, well...

467
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:11,620
Kind of.

468
00:24:12,110 --> 00:24:13,000
It's nothing, really.

469
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:16,490
Mm...

470
00:24:16,520 --> 00:24:18,800
We hadn't met each other at all in France.

471
00:24:19,480 --> 00:24:21,280
We even went to the same school, too.

472
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:23,080
I know, right?

473
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:24,840
Strange, isn't it?

474
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:27,820
Perhaps

475
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:31,360
we'd been walking on a different path.

476
00:24:33,290 --> 00:24:34,100
But look,

477
00:24:34,530 --> 00:24:35,840
we're on the same path now.

478
00:24:38,870 --> 00:24:39,830
You're right.

479
00:24:42,420 --> 00:24:46,320
But we don't know how long
it will be before our path diverges.

480
00:24:48,940 --> 00:24:51,280
If we share preferences,

481
00:24:51,660 --> 00:24:53,400
we can walk the same path
together for a long time.

482
00:24:57,410 --> 00:24:58,410
What are you into, though?

483
00:25:01,590 --> 00:25:02,710
Well...

484
00:25:02,940 --> 00:25:04,680
Clothes,

485
00:25:04,890 --> 00:25:06,080
sunlight,

486
00:25:06,490 --> 00:25:08,040
nature,

487
00:25:08,810 --> 00:25:10,110
and random chit-chatting.

488
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:12,780
Also...

489
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:16,290
Should I say, "I'm into you," too?

490
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:23,560
Hey, I'm kidding.

491
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,560
Don't look so pale now.

492
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:32,880
Mm... But...

493
00:25:33,830 --> 00:25:35,680
I'm actually into you, Gale.

494
00:25:37,350 --> 00:25:38,310
I don't know.

495
00:25:38,340 --> 00:25:39,480
I just feel like

496
00:25:40,030 --> 00:25:41,590
I'm comfortable talking to you,

497
00:25:43,460 --> 00:25:45,110
as if we've been close friends for ages.

498
00:25:46,210 --> 00:25:48,880
Although we haven't
known each other for even a month,

499
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:51,780
it feels like we've been close for years.

500
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:55,700
I love having a friend like you.

501
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:02,920
Hey, Gale.

502
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:03,920
Are you good?

503
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:05,820
Did I say something wrong?

504
00:26:06,930 --> 00:26:07,590
No.

505
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,100
I'm not used to this.

506
00:26:11,700 --> 00:26:13,680
Not many people have said
something like this to me.

507
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:16,220
Mm.

508
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:19,600
What if I say it to you every day?

509
00:26:20,930 --> 00:26:21,930
Will you get used to it?

510
00:26:27,900 --> 00:26:29,240
It'd be nice if you could.

511
00:26:38,290 --> 00:26:39,190
Ladies,

512
00:26:39,450 --> 00:26:40,810
would you like some rice noodles?

513
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:42,720
My curry is to die for.

514
00:26:43,020 --> 00:26:44,430
Oh, the curry.

515
00:26:44,690 --> 00:26:45,880
Have you had it since you came here?

516
00:26:46,150 --> 00:26:47,080
Shall we have it?

517
00:26:47,530 --> 00:26:48,190
Come on.

518
00:26:59,110 --> 00:27:00,110
Wait for me at the car.

519
00:27:15,630 --> 00:27:17,210
I know you hate surprises,

520
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:19,920
but maybe

521
00:27:20,830 --> 00:27:22,310
a private conversation

522
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:24,900
will give you more than you expected.

523
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:26,380
What is it?

524
00:27:26,420 --> 00:27:27,420
You already know.

525
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:31,100
But I'm here today as
someone offering you options,

526
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:33,970
not your enemy

527
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:35,800
or competitor.

528
00:27:40,060 --> 00:27:42,080
I know you're closing the deal with K Group,

529
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:46,000
a deal so massive it will
change the Thai tea industry as a whole.

530
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,240
But consider this.

531
00:27:50,620 --> 00:27:52,110
If Khum Rimpha

532
00:27:53,370 --> 00:27:55,100
agrees to step back
from the domestic market,

533
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:58,120
stop competing,

534
00:27:58,510 --> 00:27:59,590
refrain from price-cutting,

535
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:02,540
and hand over some export rights

536
00:28:03,410 --> 00:28:04,900
to Phusangdao Farm,

537
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:08,720
you'll gain far more than you've imagined.

538
00:28:11,280 --> 00:28:12,720
On one condition, however.

539
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,000
You must let me take this deal.

540
00:28:26,900 --> 00:28:28,180
This is...

541
00:28:29,550 --> 00:28:30,590
an offer,

542
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,300
not an ultimatum.

543
00:28:48,650 --> 00:28:49,980
But let me guess,

544
00:28:51,410 --> 00:28:53,720
if I decline your offer,

545
00:28:55,750 --> 00:28:58,280
someone like you
will find another way to get in my way.

546
00:28:58,800 --> 00:28:59,600
Precisely.

547
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,190
I'm a businessman, just like you.

548
00:29:04,700 --> 00:29:05,640
Consider the offer.

549
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:28,410
This is basically a merger.

550
00:29:29,450 --> 00:29:32,360
You're offering me a seat at your table

551
00:29:34,050 --> 00:29:36,400
just to flip the board
and win the game in the end.

552
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,730
It's a win-win in other people's eyes.

553
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:39,940
What about this in your eyes?

554
00:29:41,810 --> 00:29:43,290
In my eyes?

555
00:29:45,390 --> 00:29:47,590
I just want others in the industry to see

556
00:29:48,410 --> 00:29:50,110
that we are on good terms.

557
00:29:51,410 --> 00:29:52,490
No need to compete;

558
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:54,920
I'll simply swallow you whole,

559
00:29:56,930 --> 00:29:58,640
bit by bit.

560
00:30:00,290 --> 00:30:02,010
And one day, your name

561
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,610
will be nothing but a tiny logo
under our conglomerate.

562
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,110
What a brilliant offer this is.

563
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:13,120
But you must have forgotten something.

564
00:30:17,900 --> 00:30:18,900
Trust.

565
00:30:20,750 --> 00:30:23,440
A business model built on mutual distrust

566
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:26,780
is not a joint venture in my book.

567
00:30:29,290 --> 00:30:30,380
It's a trap.

568
00:30:35,140 --> 00:30:37,680
Your scheme is just like this cup of tea.

569
00:30:41,290 --> 00:30:42,490
It's fragrant,

570
00:30:43,190 --> 00:30:45,280
but you don't really know what is in it.

571
00:30:47,820 --> 00:30:49,100
Remember this:

572
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:53,100
never think of yourself as a player.

573
00:30:54,150 --> 00:30:55,630
Sometimes,

574
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:58,040
a pawn is just a pawn,

575
00:30:59,200 --> 00:31:00,860
but the one who wins

576
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:04,100
is the one who establishes the board.

577
00:31:05,260 --> 00:31:06,360
And what about you?

578
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:08,480
What role do you play

579
00:31:09,100 --> 00:31:10,680
on this board?

580
00:31:12,890 --> 00:31:15,100
I'm tired of being compared
to a pawn by others.

581
00:31:16,930 --> 00:31:19,000
I'll be the hand that moves the pieces now.

582
00:31:19,890 --> 00:31:21,610
Then I'll let you in on something.

583
00:31:24,190 --> 00:31:26,030
Being the hand that moves the pieces

584
00:31:27,690 --> 00:31:30,790
is far riskier than just
being a piece on the board.

585
00:31:39,390 --> 00:31:41,680
Phusangdao Farm has never played
anyone else's game

586
00:31:42,980 --> 00:31:44,810
because we have a board of our own.

587
00:32:21,350 --> 00:32:23,480
You're... Mueanphae, right?

588
00:32:24,470 --> 00:32:26,620
- She's the girl who you...
- Oh! This is...

589
00:32:27,850 --> 00:32:28,870
Jessica,

590
00:32:28,910 --> 00:32:30,400
a friend of mine from Paris.

591
00:32:38,210 --> 00:32:39,480
She sure is lovely.

592
00:33:02,580 --> 00:33:03,680
Wow.

593
00:33:06,310 --> 00:33:07,880
How long has it been?

594
00:33:09,130 --> 00:33:11,160
I missed being there.

595
00:33:11,290 --> 00:33:12,620
Let me see...

596
00:33:16,780 --> 00:33:18,830
This is what Brook gave me.

597
00:33:27,290 --> 00:33:28,220
Aw.

598
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,000
This is cute.

599
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:35,680
I couldn't remember having this.

600
00:33:45,010 --> 00:33:46,090
Where did these come from?

601
00:33:52,920 --> 00:33:54,810
A congratulations letter.

602
00:34:17,699 --> 00:34:19,100
A clover leaf?

603
00:34:43,110 --> 00:34:44,600
I thought you said you can't remember me.

604
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:15,440
[To Phae]

605
00:35:25,590 --> 00:35:26,440
Whoa.

606
00:35:35,280 --> 00:35:36,280
Mok,

607
00:35:36,370 --> 00:35:37,570
why are you standing there?

608
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,060
Come sit and eat.

609
00:35:39,180 --> 00:35:39,850
Yeah.

610
00:35:39,890 --> 00:35:41,590
And share the fried chicken with us, too.

611
00:35:41,620 --> 00:35:43,280
- Yeah.
- Are you planning to eat all of it?

612
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:44,770
Let's eat.

613
00:35:44,820 --> 00:35:45,820
I want the wing.

614
00:35:47,610 --> 00:35:49,120
Oh, fried chicken.

615
00:35:55,240 --> 00:35:56,490
Bring me some vegetables.

616
00:35:59,620 --> 00:36:00,930
Let's eat.

617
00:36:01,830 --> 00:36:03,950
- Looks great.
- Very tasty.

618
00:36:06,820 --> 00:36:08,470
Come, come, come.

619
00:36:21,640 --> 00:36:22,880
Mok, Seang.

620
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:24,000
- Yes?
- Yes, Auntie?

621
00:36:24,260 --> 00:36:26,400
Go call Saitharn to come eat.

622
00:36:27,000 --> 00:36:28,720
I already finished eating. I'll go.

623
00:36:28,890 --> 00:36:29,700
Alright.

624
00:36:37,780 --> 00:36:39,040
Give me the cucumber.

625
00:36:42,940 --> 00:36:43,840
Saitharn.

626
00:36:44,400 --> 00:36:45,490
Saitharn!

627
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:46,700
Saitharn.

628
00:36:46,930 --> 00:36:48,460
Auntie Nong asked me to take you to eat!

629
00:36:48,500 --> 00:36:50,010
You haven't eaten anything, have you?!

630
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:58,990
Saitharn, can you hear me?!

631
00:37:03,260 --> 00:37:04,400
Where is he?

632
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:17,680
What?!

633
00:37:18,450 --> 00:37:19,480
Fried meat?

634
00:37:21,650 --> 00:37:22,720
Well,

635
00:37:23,050 --> 00:37:25,400
this is what people from here usually eat.

636
00:37:26,190 --> 00:37:28,520
We're sitting in the open to eat

637
00:37:28,900 --> 00:37:30,480
without needing to hide anything.

638
00:37:31,170 --> 00:37:32,720
I'll sit and eat with you here

639
00:37:33,020 --> 00:37:34,360
so that the entire farm knows.

640
00:37:36,330 --> 00:37:39,680
There's also some tea wine
from S Club you like.

641
00:37:41,110 --> 00:37:41,900
Wait.

642
00:37:42,850 --> 00:37:43,850
How did you know that?

643
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:46,710
Well, when we first met,

644
00:37:47,330 --> 00:37:49,720
didn't you finish every single drop
of it off my body?

645
00:37:52,380 --> 00:37:53,120
Well...

646
00:37:54,500 --> 00:37:57,240
the wine from Phusangdao Farm
is really good.

647
00:37:59,500 --> 00:38:00,860
If it's good...

648
00:38:02,050 --> 00:38:03,000
would you care for another round?

649
00:38:19,060 --> 00:38:20,040
Let's play a game, shall we?

650
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:21,600
Truth or Drink.

651
00:38:22,710 --> 00:38:24,040
If you don't want to answer,

652
00:38:24,740 --> 00:38:25,390
you'll have to drink.

653
00:38:28,300 --> 00:38:29,300
Alright.

654
00:38:30,710 --> 00:38:31,920
Since you suggested it...

655
00:38:32,400 --> 00:38:33,830
I'll let you go first.

656
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:40,280
What did you study?

657
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:42,820
Business Management,
but I wasn't good at it,

658
00:38:42,850 --> 00:38:44,130
so I couldn't manage my family's business.

659
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:44,640
What about you?

660
00:38:44,670 --> 00:38:45,990
Agricultural Management.

661
00:38:47,960 --> 00:38:48,800
Fitting.

662
00:38:51,260 --> 00:38:51,920
So...

663
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:53,880
have you considered doing something else?

664
00:38:58,000 --> 00:38:59,240
I don't have a choice.

665
00:39:01,100 --> 00:39:02,640
My father loved this farm,

666
00:39:04,620 --> 00:39:07,110
and I simply want to make him proud.

667
00:39:11,590 --> 00:39:13,610
I want him to see me in this moment.

668
00:39:20,550 --> 00:39:22,380
He should be proud of you.

669
00:39:26,700 --> 00:39:27,350
So,

670
00:39:27,720 --> 00:39:28,500
what about you then?

671
00:39:28,890 --> 00:39:29,700
Your family.

672
00:39:33,980 --> 00:39:35,510
Mom said that I'm a troublemaker.

673
00:39:35,850 --> 00:39:36,840
I'm not smart,

674
00:39:37,490 --> 00:39:38,700
I can't work,

675
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,680
and I don't have any skills.

676
00:39:41,190 --> 00:39:43,120
I just live day by day.

677
00:39:47,710 --> 00:39:49,040
But now,

678
00:39:49,890 --> 00:39:51,300
you're getting better
at harvesting tea leaves.

679
00:39:53,610 --> 00:39:55,300
Have you ever heard of this?

680
00:39:55,360 --> 00:39:56,610
"If you aren't born talented,

681
00:39:57,420 --> 00:39:58,360
make up for it with effort."

682
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:03,790
Thank you.

683
00:40:04,720 --> 00:40:05,960
But that quote

684
00:40:06,570 --> 00:40:07,880
is so lame.

685
00:40:09,460 --> 00:40:10,760
It's what Gen Yers would say.

686
00:40:11,100 --> 00:40:12,340
Next question.

687
00:40:12,520 --> 00:40:13,700
- Love life.
- Nope.

688
00:40:14,430 --> 00:40:15,320
I'm skipping this one.

689
00:40:19,830 --> 00:40:21,620
You just have to say it.
It's not that hard.

690
00:40:25,300 --> 00:40:26,300
Tell me about your first love.

691
00:40:30,170 --> 00:40:31,360
It's easy for you...

692
00:40:31,610 --> 00:40:32,860
to say that.

693
00:40:34,870 --> 00:40:36,040
You say it first.

694
00:40:43,630 --> 00:40:44,630
Well...

695
00:40:45,090 --> 00:40:47,860
I'm not sure
if it's really what you'd call a first love.

696
00:40:50,100 --> 00:40:52,100
But the first person I was fond of

697
00:40:52,520 --> 00:40:53,400
was a woman.

698
00:40:55,790 --> 00:40:58,640
But as I grew up, I realized

699
00:40:59,130 --> 00:41:00,810
that it wasn't a romantic feeling.

700
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:04,320
Back then, when my father forced me...

701
00:41:05,490 --> 00:41:06,960
to marry her,

702
00:41:10,060 --> 00:41:11,580
we had a huge argument.

703
00:41:13,150 --> 00:41:14,790
Let's just say
our relationship was in shambles.

704
00:41:15,570 --> 00:41:17,960
All because I'm not straight.

705
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:23,020
After that, I dated a junior
from my university.

706
00:41:23,870 --> 00:41:25,760
That was my first time dating a guy.

707
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:30,560
We openly dated

708
00:41:30,600 --> 00:41:33,480
because I believed that it would last.

709
00:41:38,080 --> 00:41:40,680
Still, it didn't work out.

710
00:41:43,160 --> 00:41:44,270
Hey...

711
00:41:45,150 --> 00:41:46,290
You don't have to tell me anymore.

712
00:41:47,970 --> 00:41:48,580
Well,

713
00:41:49,230 --> 00:41:51,420
that made my father even more upset,

714
00:41:54,170 --> 00:41:56,000
and we didn't come to an understanding,

715
00:41:57,400 --> 00:41:58,600
not before he passed.

716
00:42:05,310 --> 00:42:07,260
I think that perhaps love

717
00:42:08,210 --> 00:42:10,610
is the memory of a time

718
00:42:12,340 --> 00:42:13,430
when we were happy.

719
00:42:13,470 --> 00:42:17,100
A reminder that you used to be
a crucial part of someone's life.

720
00:42:19,310 --> 00:42:20,520
It's just my opinion.

721
00:42:23,160 --> 00:42:24,160
And...

722
00:42:25,940 --> 00:42:27,720
have you ever felt
like that toward someone?

723
00:42:37,400 --> 00:42:38,100
Hey.

724
00:42:38,930 --> 00:42:39,630
Wait,

725
00:42:40,050 --> 00:42:41,320
why didn't you answer that?

726
00:42:42,190 --> 00:42:43,540
Are you trying to avoid the question, too?

727
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:49,690
Because that person
hasn't realized just yet

728
00:42:51,620 --> 00:42:53,430
that he is someone important to me.

729
00:42:54,630 --> 00:43:00,000
♫Once in a lifetime,♫

730
00:43:00,230 --> 00:43:03,680
♫I don't care if it's right or wrong♫

731
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:08,960
♫Even if it breaks my heart,
I've given it my all♫

732
00:43:09,500 --> 00:43:10,300
Well?

733
00:43:14,460 --> 00:43:15,460
What?

734
00:43:18,290 --> 00:43:18,880
Oh?

735
00:43:19,490 --> 00:43:20,610
Why did you drink?

736
00:43:21,370 --> 00:43:22,720
I haven't even asked you anything.

737
00:43:24,970 --> 00:43:26,200
I was just thirsty.

738
00:43:28,570 --> 00:43:29,230
So,

739
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:32,080
your first time having sex?

740
00:43:33,280 --> 00:43:34,040
Huh?

741
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:35,470
Come on.

742
00:43:36,770 --> 00:43:38,590
Alright, no more questions.

743
00:43:39,750 --> 00:43:42,220
But you have to call me

744
00:43:43,230 --> 00:43:44,270
"Boss" first.

745
00:43:45,380 --> 00:43:46,640
If you don't,

746
00:43:47,290 --> 00:43:48,790
you have to drink the whole glass.

747
00:44:05,740 --> 00:44:06,500
Come on.

748
00:44:07,990 --> 00:44:08,770
Boss.

749
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:10,760
Boss.

750
00:44:12,660 --> 00:44:14,580
Boss...

751
00:44:15,880 --> 00:44:17,440
Boss.

752
00:44:17,940 --> 00:44:19,490
Boss.

753
00:44:20,770 --> 00:44:21,580
No.

754
00:44:22,510 --> 00:44:23,800
Boss.

755
00:44:23,830 --> 00:44:24,870
Boss.

756
00:44:24,900 --> 00:44:25,820
Boss.

757
00:44:25,860 --> 00:44:26,760
Boss.

758
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:29,720
Fine, Boss.

759
00:44:29,920 --> 00:44:30,520
Boss.

760
00:44:30,720 --> 00:44:32,080
Boss, Boss, Boss.

761
00:44:32,110 --> 00:44:33,210
Boss, Boss.

762
00:45:53,230 --> 00:45:54,330
Hey.

763
00:45:57,210 --> 00:45:58,100
Hey.

764
00:45:59,730 --> 00:46:00,730
Hey?

765
00:46:03,800 --> 00:46:04,600
Hey?

766
00:46:45,660 --> 00:46:47,600
You seem to get along with everyone.

767
00:46:47,940 --> 00:46:49,080
Have you gotten used to being here?

768
00:46:49,900 --> 00:46:51,080
At first, I thought

769
00:46:51,820 --> 00:46:53,400
it wouldn't be all that great.

770
00:46:53,480 --> 00:46:55,300
But being here is far better...

771
00:46:55,330 --> 00:46:57,000
than just sitting around

772
00:46:57,290 --> 00:46:58,960
and doing nothing in Bangkok.

773
00:46:59,480 --> 00:47:02,570
Do you plan to leave
after paying me all your debt?

774
00:47:04,910 --> 00:47:06,400
I have some work for you to do.

775
00:47:22,320 --> 00:47:28,140
♫I wanna thank you for making me feel♫

776
00:47:28,180 --> 00:47:31,760
♫Just how beautiful love can be♫

777
00:47:31,780 --> 00:47:34,000
♫Every chamber of my heart♫

778
00:47:34,020 --> 00:47:36,640
♫Will be yours from now on♫

779
00:47:36,660 --> 00:47:42,300
♫You're a godsent present from above♫

780
00:47:42,500 --> 00:47:48,320
♫I'll always belong to you evermore♫

781
00:47:48,340 --> 00:47:54,540
♫My heart will always be yours forever♫

